author: @HaiWorldz
text:
Wonwoo's singing voice is sublime!!! Not to mention he has the cutest outfit on!! Yellow bandana for the win!!!
Joshua looks extra cute in his yellow and white overalls while dancing to this song. 
Minghao is being extra by leading a dab group with his eye-catching red hair.
Seungcheol looks like an angel in his pink and white outfit+ black hair combo while rolling the lyrics so easily off his tongue.
Seokmin's high notes could cure the plague. His facial expressions and dancing go along perfectly with the song. 
Jun's little spotlight stole my heart away. That boy certainly knows what he's doing and how to get people to fall head over heels for him.
Vernon's hair + outfit combo is amazing here, I loved his rap part with Mingyu.
Seungkwan's high notes while also messing with Seokmin are the pinnacle of my life. 
Hoshi's part in the beginning melted my heart into actual goo. 
Mingyu, like the tall and goofy puppy he is, fits perfectly with this song. 
Dino really gives his all into every single song he dances to. <3
Jeonghan's hair keeps on flapping everywhere, but I just think that's super cute. His voice is really smooth, and it's improved since the past!
Woozi's voice is so calming and strong. He's so in control of his voice, it's astounding. 

I did not mean to make a list of things I liked about this video and each one of them here, but hey, sometimes you gotta do what you gotta do.  ¯\_(ツ)_/¯

text:
플레디스 관계자 분들, 슈주가 리메이크 한 것과 똑같은 버전에,조금 다른  안무에 ,제스쳐까지 거의 똑같이, 비슷하게 하면서 어느 가수 버전을 커버 했는지 표기를 안 하신 것은 상당히 도리에 맞지 않다고 봅니다. 
당장 여기 댓글만 봐도 세븐틴 분들이 부른 '행복'이 신곡인줄 아시는 분들도 계시더군요. 제목 밑에 눈에 띄지도 않게 해시태그로만 '#슈퍼주니어' 이렇게 쓸게 아니라 슈주도 H.O.T 분들 노래를 리메이크 한거라 애매하시다면 '슈퍼주니어ver.' 이런식으로 제목에 다시 써주시길 부탁드리고 이에 대한 사과도 해주시길 바랍니다. 빠른 피드백 기다리겠습니다.

text: woah, woah, woah, woah. Here I was expecting a new song, but instead I got slapped with 15 doses of nostalgia. wtf. wtf. wtf I feel like crying. I'm reminiscing on my baby kpop days when I was 10 years old dancing to the SMTOWN Summer Album (yes you young ones, SMTOWN used to have YEARLY summer and winter albums. The consistency stopped around 2008) when Super Junior sang a cover of this song. This song is so fucking old, but it never disappoints. From one thirteen member group to another (Super Junior to Seventeen, although this is originally an H.O.T song), from one bias group to another. SO HAPPY SO HAPPY SO HAPPY. HONESTLY TEARS OF JOY RUNNING DOWN MY FACE RIGHT NOW. THIS COVER MEANS EVERYTHING TO ME.
